{"saves":{},"saveIDs":[],"portraits":{"05027912-f8b1-45ff-b074-8e4fce02cf4a":"","3ef85492-2bf9-4cb2-bf0f-20d9ecc22700":"","aff52ed1-59ae-4039-8801-61214e2d70e1":"","bfd99ae4-935f-4ca6-8bfe-98113a2af9cf":""},"customFiles":{"005debef-3ea6-4273-9591-a72118cd797d":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"005debef-3ea6-4273-9591-a72118cd797d\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Deceptive Tactics\\\",\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Requirements</b> You can prepare at least two tactics.<br><br>Your training has taught you that the art of war is the art of deception. You can use your Warfare Lore modifier in place of your Deception modifier for Deception checks to Create a Diversion or Feint, and can use your proficiency rank in Warfare Lore instead of your proficiency rank in Deception to meet the prerequisites of feats that modify the Create a Diversion or Feint actions (such as Lengthy Diversion). You gain the Lengthy Diversion feat (Player Core 258).\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881932023\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695807\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"005debef-3ea6-4273-9591-a72118cd797d\"}","01bb6df5-b845-453f-ada2-16584ef3999f":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"01bb6df5-b845-453f-ada2-16584ef3999f\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Shield Warden\\\",\\\"level\\\":6,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"GENERAL_Shield Block\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Shield Block<br><br>When you have a shield raised, you can use your Shield Block reaction when an attack is made against an ally adjacent to you. If you do, the shield prevents that ally from taking damage instead of preventing you from taking damage, following the normal rules for Shield Block.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026510046\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":14,\\\"string0\\\":\\\"GENERAL_Shield Block\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695813\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"01bb6df5-b845-453f-ada2-16584ef3999f\"}","04e1041d-26cd-4c80-93b0-54cf836e4c63":"{\"type\":1,\"json\":\"{\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1716296105039\\\",\\\"uniqueIdentifier\\\":\\\"04e1041d-26cd-4c80-93b0-54cf836e4c63\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Int to Medicine\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Adds the difference between Wis and Int to Medicine. Make sure to update the bonus if this changes!\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"Medicine\\\",\\\"bonusType\\\":3,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":3,\\\"reference\\\":\\\"6a10ead5-0241-4f44-b37d-8eabed3ae43d\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1716753517816\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"04e1041d-26cd-4c80-93b0-54cf836e4c63\"}","05a26873-90a6-44a5-a719-87e90e73b2b6":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Stupefying Raid\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"05a26873-90a6-44a5-a719-87e90e73b2b6\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Your team dashes about in a series of maneuvers that leave the enemy befuddled. Signal up to two squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; these allies can Stride up to their Speed as a reaction. Each enemy they are adjacent to at any point during this movement must attempt a Will save against your class DC or become stupefied 1 for 1 round (stupefied 2 on a critical failure); this is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Concentrate, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"level\\\":7,\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":2,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714447378249\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"60d5a051-6242-4d02-bdff-2c2efd98d3e8\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695824\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"05a26873-90a6-44a5-a719-87e90e73b2b6\"}","07182bba-fa79-45f2-b483-cbf3af2b87ff":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"07182bba-fa79-45f2-b483-cbf3af2b87ff\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Executioner's Volley\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":2,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"<b>Frequency</b> Once per 10 minutes<br><br>You command your squadmates to act as a lethal firing squad. You and each squadmate affected by your commander’s banner can attempt a ranged Strike as a reaction against a single target you designate; combine the damage from all attacks for the purpose of resistances and weaknesses. If the designated target is a living creature, these attacks are death effects and gain the death trait. If the designated target dies as a result of this tactic, all other enemies within the affected area of your commander’s banner must succeed at a Will save against your class DC or be frightened 2.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300701\\\",\\\"save\\\":\\\"Will\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695820\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"07182bba-fa79-45f2-b483-cbf3af2b87ff\"}","07cb95c7-5afa-4e0f-b454-d5876f1eb47b":"{\"type\":1,\"json\":\"{\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1694903192588\\\",\\\"uniqueIdentifier\\\":\\\"07cb95c7-5afa-4e0f-b454-d5876f1eb47b\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Worn Immanence - Thousand-League Sandals\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"15ft aura of +10ft status to speed\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":1,\\\"bonusType\\\":1,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1695605197595\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"07cb95c7-5afa-4e0f-b454-d5876f1eb47b\"}","07d7199d-2307-404c-adf6-82a640758e28":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"07d7199d-2307-404c-adf6-82a640758e28\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"End It!\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Incapacitation, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":2,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"<b>Requirements</b> You and your allies currently outnumber enemies on the battlefield and you or a squadmate have reduced an enemy to 0 Hit Points since the start of your last turn.<br><br>At your proclamation that victory is already at hand, your allies march forward with an authoritative stomp, scattering your enemies in terror. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; you and each ally can Step directly toward a hostile creature they are observing as a free action. Any hostile creatures within 10 feet of you or a squadmate after this movement must attempt a Will save against your class DC; on a failure they become fleeing for 1 round and on a critical failure they become fleeing for 1 round and frightened 2. This is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300701\\\",\\\"save\\\":\\\"Will\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553710922\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"07d7199d-2307-404c-adf6-82a640758e28\"}","0bbe4851-0b51-4be4-ab8a-a913d9b89f64":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0bbe4851-0b51-4be4-ab8a-a913d9b89f64\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Quickening Banner\\\",\\\"level\\\":14,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Frequency</b> Once per 10 minutes<br><br>Your banner flutters desperately, urging your allies to strike now. Each ally affected by your commander’s banner is quickened for 1 round. They can use this extra action to Strike or Stride.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Archetype, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026380380\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695811\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0bbe4851-0b51-4be4-ab8a-a913d9b89f64\"}","0c8a01e1-b5da-41a1-aa5c-52d1d2374d5c":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0c8a01e1-b5da-41a1-aa5c-52d1d2374d5c\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (End It!)\\\",\\\"action\\\":2,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the End It! Tactic to your folio.<br><br><b>Requirements</b> You and your allies currently outnumber enemies on the battlefield and you or a squadmate have reduced an enemy to 0 Hit Points since the start of your last turn.<br><br>At your proclamation that victory is already at hand, your allies march forward with an authoritative stomp, scattering your enemies in terror. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; you and each ally can Step directly toward a hostile creature they are observing as a free action. Any hostile creatures within 10 feet of you or a squadmate after this movement must attempt a Will save against your class DC; on a failure they become fleeing for 1 round and on a critical failure they become fleeing for 1 round and frightened 2. This is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881042951\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"07d7199d-2307-404c-adf6-82a640758e28\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695815\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0c8a01e1-b5da-41a1-aa5c-52d1d2374d5c\"}","0cdb5c38-3718-4b2a-8601-61b4130b7d10":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"0cdb5c38-3718-4b2a-8601-61b4130b7d10\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Strike Hard!\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":2,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"You command an ally to attack. Choose a squadmate who can see or hear your signal. That ally immediately attempts a Strike as a reaction. \\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300702\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695821\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0cdb5c38-3718-4b2a-8601-61b4130b7d10\"}","0d916fa7-5a18-4688-98d1-80240f407fb5":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0d916fa7-5a18-4688-98d1-80240f407fb5\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Fortunate Blow\\\",\\\"level\\\":12,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"You set an enemy up for a devastating follow-through from your allies. Attempt a Strike against an opponent. If the Strike hits, the next creature other than you to attack the same target before the start of your next turn rolls twice on their attack roll and takes the higher result; this is a fortune effect.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, Flourish, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026192659\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695809\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0d916fa7-5a18-4688-98d1-80240f407fb5\"}","0e191611-250e-4094-a117-5e79014fe63b":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0e191611-250e-4094-a117-5e79014fe63b\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Mountaineering Training)\\\",\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Mountaineering Training Tactic to your folio.<br><br>Your instructions make it easier for you and your allies to scale dangerous surfaces. Signal all squadmates; until the end of your next turn, you and each ally gains a climb Speed of 20 feet.<br><br><b>Special</b> If you have this tactic prepared, you can use Warfare Lore in place of Athletics for checks you make to Climb.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026753914\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"3324f1b3-c709-4e0f-9d80-5d5d53df96a5\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695816\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0e191611-250e-4094-a117-5e79014fe63b\"}","0e3c84cb-8899-45d7-bac1-1ee02ea31dca":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0e3c84cb-8899-45d7-bac1-1ee02ea31dca\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Stupefying Raid)\\\",\\\"level\\\":7,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Stupefying Raid Tactic to your folio.<br><br>Your team dashes about in a series of maneuvers that leave the enemy befuddled. Signal up to two squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; these allies can Stride up to their Speed as a reaction. Each enemy they are adjacent to at any point during this movement must attempt a Will save against your class DC or become stupefied 1 for 1 round (stupefied 2 on a critical failure); this is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026899553\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"23a09c02-1feb-400e-a7b7-d0cc7e04b4b7\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695818\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0e3c84cb-8899-45d7-bac1-1ee02ea31dca\"}","0f13e454-aa68-4c91-b562-368cc07ebea9":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"0f13e454-aa68-4c91-b562-368cc07ebea9\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Reactive Interference\\\",\\\"level\\\":12,\\\"action\\\":0,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Trigger</b> An adjacent enemy begins to use a reaction.<br><br>Your own tactical expertise allows you to quickly identify and prevent enemy responses. If the triggering creature’s level is equal to or lower than yours, you disrupt the triggering reaction. If the triggering creature’s level is higher than yours, make an attack roll against its AC. On a success, you disrupt the reaction.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026414566\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695812\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"0f13e454-aa68-4c91-b562-368cc07ebea9\"}","12aac5fd-1bb4-4aea-86ee-2e305905695e":"{\"type\":1,\"json\":\"{\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1694903192589\\\",\\\"uniqueIdentifier\\\":\\\"12aac5fd-1bb4-4aea-86ee-2e305905695e\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Weapon Immanence - Barrow's Edge\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"+1 persistent spirit damage per die from weapon ikon\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":4,\\\"bonusType\\\":3,\\\"listDamTraits\\\":[\\\"Ikon\\\"]}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1695605197596\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"12aac5fd-1bb4-4aea-86ee-2e305905695e\"}","1310dc23-0008-4473-9b60-a1410050892e":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1310dc23-0008-4473-9b60-a1410050892e\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Drilled Reflexes\\\",\\\"level\\\":10,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"a5022302-88f8-482d-bf8d-ea58424bdd5b||e699292c-51b0-462a-90fc-d6919a067981\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Drilled Reactions<br><br>You leave a lasting impression on your squadmates that makes them particularly adept at following your commands. When you use your drilled reactions ability, you can give an extra reaction to up to two allies instead of only one.<br>\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026169546\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695809\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1310dc23-0008-4473-9b60-a1410050892e\"}","135393ba-6da9-434e-b0a0-18565528a44e":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"135393ba-6da9-434e-b0a0-18565528a44e\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Shield Warden\\\",\\\"level\\\":6,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"GENERAL_Shield Block\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Shield Block<br><br>When you have a shield raised, you can use your Shield Block reaction when an attack is made against an ally adjacent to you. If you do, the shield prevents that ally from taking damage instead of preventing you from taking damage, following the normal rules for Shield Block.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880856419\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695813\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"135393ba-6da9-434e-b0a0-18565528a44e\"}","168af239-fe96-42c9-8276-20739b35f71e":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"168af239-fe96-42c9-8276-20739b35f71e\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Fortunate Blow\\\",\\\"level\\\":12,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"You set an enemy up for a devastating follow-through from your allies. Attempt a Strike against an opponent. If the Strike hits, the next creature other than you to attack the same target before the start of your next turn rolls twice on their attack roll and takes the higher result; this is a fortune effect.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Flourish, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880604245\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695809\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"168af239-fe96-42c9-8276-20739b35f71e\"}","181dda99-f2c8-44b8-8311-a3f07e530bfb":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Legendary Tactics\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"181dda99-f2c8-44b8-8311-a3f07e530bfb\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Tactics available to Commanders with the Legendary Tactician feature.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"level\\\":19,\\\"specialType\\\":-1,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714446859275\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695823\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"181dda99-f2c8-44b8-8311-a3f07e530bfb\"}","1a3c2029-c1fe-4542-8da2-00b87cd593ef":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1a3c2029-c1fe-4542-8da2-00b87cd593ef\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Deceptive Tactics\\\",\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Requirements</b> You can prepare at least two tactics.<br><br>Your training has taught you that the art of war is the art of deception. You can use your Warfare Lore modifier in place of your Deception modifier for Deception checks to Create a Diversion or Feint, and can use your proficiency rank in Warfare Lore instead of your proficiency rank in Deception to meet the prerequisites of feats that modify the Create a Diversion or Feint actions (such as Lengthy Diversion). You gain the Lengthy Diversion feat (Player Core 258).\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714882031188\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":14,\\\"string0\\\":\\\"GENERAL_Lengthy Diversion\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695807\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1a3c2029-c1fe-4542-8da2-00b87cd593ef\"}","1aa30f49-fec3-4f22-a047-08897bf6bb32":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Reload!\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"1aa30f49-fec3-4f22-a047-08897bf6bb32\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Your drill instruction kicks in and your allies rapidly reload their weapons to prepare for the next volley. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can immediately Interact to reload as a reaction. <br><br><b>Special</b> When leading a siege weapon crew (Guns &amp; Gears 72), you can use this tactic to command your squadmates to Load a siege weapon instead.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714447773378\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"807726c4-dc3d-4140-9385-434b2fa22b4a\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695824\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1aa30f49-fec3-4f22-a047-08897bf6bb32\"}","1c49e5df-8a4b-420f-9a2c-47aa8eb001f3":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1c49e5df-8a4b-420f-9a2c-47aa8eb001f3\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion\\\",\\\"level\\\":2,\\\"selectable\\\":20,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Your folio is filled with tactics and techniques you’ve devised based on study and experience. Add two additional tactics you qualify for to your folio.<br><br><b>Special</b>  You can take this feat multiple times, adding two new tactics to your folio each time.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026573562\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695813\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1c49e5df-8a4b-420f-9a2c-47aa8eb001f3\"}","1cba80e4-49a8-4428-940b-2513376602f0":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1cba80e4-49a8-4428-940b-2513376602f0\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Pincer Attack)\\\",\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Pincer Attack Tactic to your folio.<br><br>You signal an aggressive formation designed to exploit enemies’ vulnerabilities. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can Step as a free action. If any of your allies end this movement adjacent to an opponent, that opponent is off-guard to melee attacks from you and all other squadmates who responded to Pincer Attack until the start of your next turn.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881142305\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"4baeb5fb-2a6f-433f-a382-293003671100\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695817\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1cba80e4-49a8-4428-940b-2513376602f0\"}","1ddbe8e7-93cf-4b86-80f5-2bcd388aebba":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1ddbe8e7-93cf-4b86-80f5-2bcd388aebba\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Warfare Expertise\\\",\\\"level\\\":3,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Your knowledge of war and strategy grows and guides your decisions in battle. You gain expert proficiency in Warfare Lore. <br><br>You can use Warfare Lore to Recall Knowledge about most creatures regardless of type, but typically only to determine whether they can be reasoned with, their most notable offensive abilities, and whether one of their saving throws is particularly weak.<br><br>The GM can decide to allow additional questions to be answered when Recalling Knowledge with Warfare Lore as appropriate to the situation. In addition, as long as you are observing at least one opponent when initiative is rolled, you can use Warfare Lore for your initiative roll.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715032466071\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"Lore: Warfare\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":11,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":4}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695819\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1ddbe8e7-93cf-4b86-80f5-2bcd388aebba\"}","1fa73ec1-408c-4d84-bbe4-de0e5eacd9a6":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1fa73ec1-408c-4d84-bbe4-de0e5eacd9a6\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Executioner's Volley)\\\",\\\"level\\\":19,\\\"action\\\":2,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Executioner's Volley Tactic to your folio.<br><br><b>Frequency</b> Once per 10 minutes<br><br>You command your squadmates to act as a lethal firing squad. You and each squadmate affected by your commander’s banner can attempt a ranged Strike as a reaction against a single target you designate; combine the damage from all attacks for the purpose of resistances and weaknesses. If the designated target is a living creature, these attacks are death effects and gain the death trait. If the designated target dies as a result of this tactic, all other enemies within the affected area of your commander’s banner must succeed at a Will save against your class DC or be frightened 2.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881055684\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"07182bba-fa79-45f2-b483-cbf3af2b87ff\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695815\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1fa73ec1-408c-4d84-bbe4-de0e5eacd9a6\"}","1fda9f83-6d5e-4be0-8cf8-2fca12c3da24":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"1fda9f83-6d5e-4be0-8cf8-2fca12c3da24\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Form Up!)\\\",\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Form Up! Tactic to your folio.<br><br>You signal your team to move into position together. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can immediately Stride as a reaction, though each must end their movement inside your banner’s aura.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026734836\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"60712abb-4212-4d3c-948c-9902f23eaae9\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695815\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"1fda9f83-6d5e-4be0-8cf8-2fca12c3da24\"}","212c851d-625e-4902-846b-edb96e27186e":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"212c851d-625e-4902-846b-edb96e27186e\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Unrivaled Analysis\\\",\\\"level\\\":8,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"40deb837-a791-4645-b155-526b4e3cff99||3e1c3f57-1969-4898-b61d-3e766dd42425\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Rapid Assessment<br><br>Your experience allows you to derive even more information about your opponents from a mere glance. When you use Rapid Assessment, you can attempt up to four checks to Recall Knowledge about creatures you are observing.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026991894\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695819\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"212c851d-625e-4902-846b-edb96e27186e\"}","21e1a03a-3578-4058-9299-e6c349bfe12d":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Expert Spellcasting\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"21e1a03a-3578-4058-9299-e6c349bfe12d\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"your proficiency rank for spell attacks and spell DC increases to expert.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"level\\\":9,\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"Divine\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":11,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":4,\\\"reference\\\":\\\"f1cbfe74-e332-4e22-8955-0b9b6d4cdffb\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1722225244471\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"21e1a03a-3578-4058-9299-e6c349bfe12d\"}","235024b4-461d-4160-99f0-65393bb7097b":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"235024b4-461d-4160-99f0-65393bb7097b\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Commander's Steed\\\",\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"You gain the service of a young animal companion as a mount. See Animal Companions (Player Core 206). You can affix your banner to your mount’s saddle or barding, determining the effects of your commander’s banner and other abilities that use your banner from your mount’s space, even if you are not currently riding your mount. Typically, the steed is an animal companion with the mount ability (such as a horse).\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715033727002\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":14,\\\"string0\\\":\\\"DRUID_Animal Companion\\\",\\\"reference\\\":\\\"943e3c5f-7189-43fc-9b88-43255d2e5d80\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695806\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"235024b4-461d-4160-99f0-65393bb7097b\"}","23a09c02-1feb-400e-a7b7-d0cc7e04b4b7":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"23a09c02-1feb-400e-a7b7-d0cc7e04b4b7\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Stupefying Raid\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"Your team dashes about in a series of maneuvers that leave the enemy befuddled. Signal up to two squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; these allies can Stride up to their Speed as a reaction. Each enemy they are adjacent to at any point during this movement must attempt a Will save against your class DC or become stupefied 1 for 1 round (stupefied 2 on a critical failure); this is an emotion, fear, and mental effect.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300702\\\",\\\"save\\\":\\\"Will\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695821\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"23a09c02-1feb-400e-a7b7-d0cc7e04b4b7\"}","241ce73e-78dc-4241-930b-e4b71a28566f":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"241ce73e-78dc-4241-930b-e4b71a28566f\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Strike Hard!)\\\",\\\"action\\\":2,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Strike Hard! Tactic to your folio.<br><br>You command an ally to attack. Choose a squadmate who can see or hear your signal. That ally immediately attempts a Strike as a reaction. \\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026886010\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"0cdb5c38-3718-4b2a-8601-61b4130b7d10\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695818\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"241ce73e-78dc-4241-930b-e4b71a28566f\"}","27dce8cd-2656-4c94-a209-275cfdc9cf2c":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"27dce8cd-2656-4c94-a209-275cfdc9cf2c\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Quickening Banner\\\",\\\"level\\\":14,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Frequency</b> Once per 10 minutes<br><br>Your banner flutters desperately, urging your allies to strike now. Each ally affected by your commander’s banner is quickened for 1 round. They can use this extra action to Strike or Stride.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880755829\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695812\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"27dce8cd-2656-4c94-a209-275cfdc9cf2c\"}","2904e446-8951-46dd-8dd4-d9cbf98a80a3":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"2904e446-8951-46dd-8dd4-d9cbf98a80a3\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Reload!\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"Your drill instruction kicks in and your allies rapidly reload their weapons to prepare for the next volley. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can immediately Interact to reload as a reaction. <br><br><b>Special</b> When leading a siege weapon crew (Guns &amp; Gears 72), you can use this tactic to command your squadmates to Load a siege weapon instead.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300701\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695821\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2904e446-8951-46dd-8dd4-d9cbf98a80a3\"}","2a300409-45e5-4ce2-8c61-9a7e3f58ec77":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"2a300409-45e5-4ce2-8c61-9a7e3f58ec77\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Ready, Aim, Fire!)\\\",\\\"level\\\":15,\\\"action\\\":2,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Ready, Aim, Fire! Tactic to your folio.<br><br>You signal a volley of ranged attacks from your allies. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; they can Interact to swap to a ranged weapon as a free action, Interact to reload as a free action, and then attempt a ranged Strike against an enemy that both you and they are observing as a reaction.<br><br><b>Special</b> If one of your squadmates knows or has prepared a cantrip with a range of 30 feet or more, they can cast it as a reaction targeting an enemy you both are observing instead of taking the other actions normally granted by this tactic.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881175487\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"5570eda5-45e9-4b1a-b203-c56109ba0814\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695817\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2a300409-45e5-4ce2-8c61-9a7e3f58ec77\"}","2ab15071-020e-4d25-bb4b-987958afc110":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Form Up!\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"2ab15071-020e-4d25-bb4b-987958afc110\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"You signal your team to move into position together. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can immediately Stride as a reaction, though each must end their movement inside your banner’s aura.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714446333049\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"807726c4-dc3d-4140-9385-434b2fa22b4a\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695823\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2ab15071-020e-4d25-bb4b-987958afc110\"}","2be38f48-4257-4060-bbd4-6205722c2c2d":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Pincer Attack\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"2be38f48-4257-4060-bbd4-6205722c2c2d\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"You signal an aggressive formation designed to exploit enemies’ vulnerabilities. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can Step as a free action. If any of your allies end this movement adjacent to an opponent, that opponent is off-guard to melee attacks from you and all other squadmates who responded to Pincer Attack until the start of your next turn.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714447727114\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"807726c4-dc3d-4140-9385-434b2fa22b4a\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695824\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2be38f48-4257-4060-bbd4-6205722c2c2d\"}","2c94ccfa-71bd-4bbf-acb6-f4882bd2ce25":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"2c94ccfa-71bd-4bbf-acb6-f4882bd2ce25\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Naval Training\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"Your instructions make it easier for you and your allies to swim through dangerous waters. Signal all squadmates; until the end of your next turn, you and each ally gains a swim Speed of 20 feet.<br><br><b>Special</b>  If you have this tactic prepared, you can use Warfare Lore in place of Athletics for checks you make to Swim.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300701\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695820\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2c94ccfa-71bd-4bbf-acb6-f4882bd2ce25\"}","2df9316c-5a74-4faa-b0d5-0badb503d708":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"2df9316c-5a74-4faa-b0d5-0badb503d708\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Coordinating Maneuvers)\\\",\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Coordinating Maneuvers Tactic to your folio.<br><br>Your team works to slip enemies into a disadvantageous position. Signal one squadmate currently affected by your commander’s banner; that ally can immediately Step as a free action. If they end this movement next to an opponent, they can attempt to Reposition that target as a reaction.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026632200\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"e5b018a6-9dae-4c38-856f-1f2b6022b727\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695814\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2df9316c-5a74-4faa-b0d5-0badb503d708\"}","2ffa89c0-7087-407e-914c-42bdb3479d11":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"2ffa89c0-7087-407e-914c-42bdb3479d11\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Confusing Commands\\\",\\\"level\\\":16,\\\"action\\\":2,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"005debef-3ea6-4273-9591-a72118cd797d||1a3c2029-c1fe-4542-8da2-00b87cd593ef\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Deceptive Tactics<br><br>You shout out bewildering but authoritative commands while imitating the voices, language, and speech patterns of your opponents. Each enemy within the area affected by your commander’s banner must succeed at a Will save against your class DC or become confused for 1 round (2 rounds on a critical failure). Targets who succeed at their saving throw are temporarily immune to Confusing Commands for 1 day.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Auditory, Commander, Archetype, Linguistic, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026060862\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695807\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"2ffa89c0-7087-407e-914c-42bdb3479d11\"}","30117d4e-aa9a-42ab-815d-a90338f340f9":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"30117d4e-aa9a-42ab-815d-a90338f340f9\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Practiced Reflexes\\\",\\\"level\\\":18,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"b9b4c0e0-c859-493d-b315-5c66f1a14782\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Drilled Reflexes<br><br>You snap out a quick series of signals or commands that urge your allies to act with alacrity. When you use your drilled reactions ability, you can give an extra reaction to up to four allies.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880739166\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695811\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"30117d4e-aa9a-42ab-815d-a90338f340f9\"}","30a1c562-ee4b-4dd9-8d05-4fe5e636f973":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"30a1c562-ee4b-4dd9-8d05-4fe5e636f973\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Glorious Banner\\\",\\\"level\\\":20,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Your banner is an awesome sight to behold. Your commander’s banner now affects a 60-foot emanation (or an 80-foot burst if you are using Plant Banner), the status bonus to Will saves and DCs against fear effects granted to your allies increases to +2, and you and affected allies gain a +1 status bonus to AC, Fortitude saves, and Reflex saves.<br><br>Enemies within the area affected by your commander’s banner take a –2 status penalty to Will saves as long as they can see your banner.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880625463\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695809\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"30a1c562-ee4b-4dd9-8d05-4fe5e636f973\"}","30aa55b3-7714-4a14-9cc8-aa99936123d9":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"30aa55b3-7714-4a14-9cc8-aa99936123d9\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Shielded Recovery\\\",\\\"level\\\":4,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"c782c199-1e14-4218-a550-05891cb959b5||c2a8d8be-c904-4eb5-b315-58164f1e196f\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Combat Medic<br><br>You can bandage wounds even while holding your shield. You can use the same hand you are using to wield a shield to Treat Wounds or use Battle Medicine, and you are considered to have a hand free for other uses of Medicine as long as the only thing you are holding or wielding in that hand is a shield. <br><br>When you use Battle Medicine on an ally while wielding a shield, they gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC and Reflex saves that lasts until the start of your next turn or until they are no longer adjacent to you, whichever comes first.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026544782\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695813\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"30aa55b3-7714-4a14-9cc8-aa99936123d9\"}","3244df0b-5570-4f97-9fcb-5d930d1b3918":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"3244df0b-5570-4f97-9fcb-5d930d1b3918\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Battle-hardened Destrier\\\",\\\"level\\\":10,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"6f82fff2-2067-404d-83ae-617508a133df\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Battle-tested War Horse<br><br>Accompanying you across countless battlefields has allowed your mount to unleash its full potential. The mount you gained with Commander’s Steed is now a nimble or savage animal companion (Player Core 211).<br><br>Your animal companion has greater independence. During an encounter, even if you don’t use the Command an Animal action, your animal companion can still use 1 action that round on your turn to Stride or Strike. It can do this at any point during your turn, as long as you aren’t currently taking an action. If it does, that’s all the actions it gets that round—you can’t Command it later.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714880304304\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695804\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3244df0b-5570-4f97-9fcb-5d930d1b3918\"}","3324f1b3-c709-4e0f-9d80-5d5d53df96a5":"{\"type\":9,\"json\":\"{\\\"uniqueID\\\":\\\"3324f1b3-c709-4e0f-9d80-5d5d53df96a5\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Mountaineering Training\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Focus\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"descriptionHeightened\\\":\\\"Your instructions make it easier for you and your allies to scale dangerous surfaces. Signal all squadmates; until the end of your next turn, you and each ally gains a climb Speed of 20 feet.<br><br><b>Special</b> If you have this tactic prepared, you can use Warfare Lore in place of Athletics for checks you make to Climb.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"focusCantrip\\\":true,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714665300701\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553710922\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3324f1b3-c709-4e0f-9d80-5d5d53df96a5\"}","3345c6fa-82dc-4235-81ec-a780b3688239":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"3345c6fa-82dc-4235-81ec-a780b3688239\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Defiant Banner\\\",\\\"level\\\":8,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"You vigorously wave your banner to remind yourself and your allies that you can and must endure. You and all allies affected by your commander’s banner when you use this action gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage equal to your Intelligence modifier until the start of your next turn. At 14th level, the value of this resistance increases to your Intelligence modifier + half your level.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Archetype, Manipulate, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881990981\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695807\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3345c6fa-82dc-4235-81ec-a780b3688239\"}","33ebe7e2-5690-4efd-a51c-935320d77265":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Master Spellcasting\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"33ebe7e2-5690-4efd-a51c-935320d77265\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"your proficiency rank for spell attacks and spell DC increases to master.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"level\\\":17,\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"Divine\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":11,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":6,\\\"reference\\\":\\\"fe4e1a25-b87e-4f56-8fa0-b96f1815d3c0\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1722225244472\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"33ebe7e2-5690-4efd-a51c-935320d77265\"}","354a0239-eb28-40bb-aac7-370afc568c84":"{\"type\":6,\"json\":\"{\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1696720501568\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"354a0239-eb28-40bb-aac7-370afc568c84\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Raised by Belief (Laws of Mortality)\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"3rd Party\\\",\\\"boost_ref_1\\\":\\\"2\\\",\\\"boost_ref_2\\\":\\\"3\\\",\\\"freeFeatID\\\":\\\"GENERAL_Assurance\\\",\\\"freeFeatDetail\\\":\\\"Medicine\\\",\\\"skill\\\":\\\"Medicine\\\",\\\"lore\\\":\\\"Laws of Mortality\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Whether in a monastery, a religious household, or just as part of your everyday life, your upbringing was steeped in the traditions of a faith or philosophy. You might have turned from your childhood creed, but your skills are still founded on your devotion.\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"limitedBoosts\\\":[2,3]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1710113234256\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"354a0239-eb28-40bb-aac7-370afc568c84\"}","35a0128e-5471-42c2-8be4-8c64a991cad9":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Coordinating Maneuvers\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"35a0128e-5471-42c2-8be4-8c64a991cad9\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Your team works to slip enemies into a disadvantageous position. Signal one squadmate currently affected by your commander’s banner; that ally can immediately Step as a free action. If they end this movement next to an opponent, they can attempt to Reposition that target as a reaction.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":1,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714447599818\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"807726c4-dc3d-4140-9385-434b2fa22b4a\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695821\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"35a0128e-5471-42c2-8be4-8c64a991cad9\"}","35b90c31-6871-4d79-acad-731d25fe446c":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"35b90c31-6871-4d79-acad-731d25fe446c\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Perfect Evaluations\\\",\\\"level\\\":12,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"c8753dc3-fd60-4194-a4ef-355e312b392f||212c851d-625e-4902-846b-edb96e27186e\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> Unrivaled Analysis<br><br>You instantly assess the strengths and weaknesses of the enemy forces. When you use Rapid Assessment, you can attempt up to six Recall Knowledge checks against enemies you are observing.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026313999\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695811\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"35b90c31-6871-4d79-acad-731d25fe446c\"}","36f3438a-3650-4737-8112-6006cc2c0887":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"36f3438a-3650-4737-8112-6006cc2c0887\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Desperate Resuscitation\\\",\\\"level\\\":14,\\\"action\\\":3,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\",\\\"GENERAL_Battle Medicine\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Prerequisites</b> master in Medicine, Combat Medic<br><b>Requirements</b> You are holding a healer's toolkit or are wearing one and have a free hand; the target's body is mostly intact.<br><br>You can use your training in combat medicine to revive the recently deceased. <br><br>Attempt a DC 40 Medicine check to revive a dead creature that has been dead for no more than 3 rounds. If you succeed, the target returns to life with the effects of raise dead, except it still has the wounded condition it had before dying, increased by 1 (or wounded 1 if it wasn’t wounded before<br>dying). <br><br>Whether you succeed or fail, the target is temporarily immune to Desperate Resuscitation for 1 day.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Archetype, Healing, Manipulate, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"hashMapRequiredProficiences\\\":{\\\"Medicine\\\":6},\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026138674\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695808\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"36f3438a-3650-4737-8112-6006cc2c0887\"}","3a752ece-0247-42eb-881b-708b2a830eb1":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"3a752ece-0247-42eb-881b-708b2a830eb1\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Pennant of Victory\\\",\\\"level\\\":20,\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Frequency</b> Once per 10 minutes<br><br>You wave your banner in writ victory, signaling to your allies that the fight is won. You and all allies affected by your commander’s banner gain a +4 status bonus to attack and damage rolls, a +10-foot status bonus to all your Speeds, and 40 temporary Hit Points. These benefits last until the start of your next turn.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Archetype, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026286858\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695810\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3a752ece-0247-42eb-881b-708b2a830eb1\"}","3c1ed3aa-d026-40ee-ac53-dc3e54596f00":"{\"type\":10,\"json\":\"{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Double Team\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"3c1ed3aa-d026-40ee-ac53-dc3e54596f00\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Your team works together to set an enemy up for a vicious attack. Signal one squadmate affected by your commander’s banner who has an opponent within their reach. That ally can Shove or Reposition an opponent as a free action. If their maneuver is successful and the target ends their movement adjacent to you or a different squadmate, you or the second squadmate can attempt a melee Strike against that target as a reaction.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, Tactic, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"specialType\\\":-2,\\\"actions\\\":2,\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714447632325\\\",\\\"parentID\\\":\\\"807726c4-dc3d-4140-9385-434b2fa22b4a\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695823\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3c1ed3aa-d026-40ee-ac53-dc3e54596f00\"}","3c747cb0-0646-4397-bb30-7c997ff3e8e8":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"3c747cb0-0646-4397-bb30-7c997ff3e8e8\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Tactical Expansion (Reload!)\\\",\\\"action\\\":1,\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"Adds the Reload! Tactic to your folio.<br><br>Your drill instruction kicks in and your allies rapidly reload their weapons to prepare for the next volley. Signal all squadmates affected by your commander’s banner; each can immediately Interact to reload as a reaction. <br><br><b>Special</b> When leading a siege weapon crew (Guns &amp; Gears 72), you can use this tactic to command your squadmates to Load a siege weapon instead.\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Commander, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Pathfinder Battlecry Playtest\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1714881188222\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"proficiencyName\\\":\\\"2904e446-8951-46dd-8dd4-d9cbf98a80a3\\\",\\\"effectType\\\":10}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695818\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3c747cb0-0646-4397-bb30-7c997ff3e8e8\"}","3d2f6fb1-e211-4a26-8359-6d26cfb340c0":"{\"type\":7,\"json\":\"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"3d2f6fb1-e211-4a26-8359-6d26cfb340c0\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Standard-bearer's Sacrifice\\\",\\\"level\\\":10,\\\"action\\\":0,\\\"reqFeats\\\":[\\\"e66394cf-55c5-48b7-85b9-4d50ad163c48\\\"],\\\"textDescription\\\":\\\"<b>Trigger</b> An opponent targets an ally with a ranged attack, you are observing both of them and you are also in range of the attack.<br><b>Requirements</b> You are holding or wielding your banner.<br><br>Seeing an enemy take aim at your ally, you bravely flourish your banner to redirect their attention to you. The triggering opponent must attempt a Will save against your class DC with the following results.<br><br><b>Success</b> The opponent completes its attack against your ally.<br><b>Failure</b> The opponent targets you with the triggering attack instead.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> As failure, but you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your AC against the triggering attack.<br>\\\",\\\"traits\\\":\\\"Banner, Commander, Archetype, Manipulate, Visual, 3rd Party\\\",\\\"src\\\":\\\"Custom\\\",\\\"databaseID\\\":1,\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1715026556165\\\"}\",\"timestamp\":\"1774553695813\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3d2f6fb1-e211-4a26-8359-6d26cfb340c0\"}","3d761a02-b07b-4c55-b24e-223a79f1dfac":"{\"type\":1,\"json\":\"{\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"1705789396114\\\",\\\"uniqueIdentifier\\\":\\\"3d761a02-b07b-4c55-b24e-223a79f1dfac\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Weapon Immanence - Titan's Breaker\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"+2 spirit damage per die. Constructs/objects not immune to the spirit damage and it bypasses any Hardness they have.\\\",\\\"listCustomEffects\\\":[{\\\"effectType\\\":4,\\\"bonusType\\\":3,\\\"bonusAmount\\\":2,\\\"listDamTraits\\\":[\\\"Ikon\\\"],\\\"reference\\\":\\\"e636bc91-51b2-4205-b5b2-bd9ad2685731\\\"}]}\",\"timestamp\":\"1710113234259\",\"uniqueIdentifier\":\"3d761a02-b07b-4c55-b24e-223a79f1dfac\"}","3db1203e-77a7-46ea-8df0-8be4992452dd":"{\"type\":101,\"json\":\"{\\\"packName\\\":\\\"Playtest_Commander\\\",\\\"packID\\\":\\\"3db1203e-77a7-46ea-8df0-8be4992452dd\\\",\\\"listPackIDS\\\":[\\\"d5a45eb0-e578-4074-b541-cc40cf155afd\\\",\\\"66849e92-bde0-40a5-b57c